**Suggestions (non-blocking improvements)**
[src/cursor/subagent-detector.ts:97] consider using the same “poll fast only after the directory exists, back off while absent” shape — Cursor needs polling more than Claude, but a fixed 500ms missing-dir scan can still become unnecessary steady-state IO.

[tests/claude-workflow/workflow-detector.test.ts:107] consider widening this remaining positive path-B wait too — it has only ~50ms of slack beyond the 500ms poll tick if `fs.watch` misses both writes.

